profile_positions.description:
Responsibilities:

- gathering intelligence in relation to organized prostitution and human trafficking criminal syndicates active in the area ;
- work as part of an investigation team, under the supervision of the team leader and assist in initiating investigations in cases of human trafficking and organized prostitution;
- gathering evidence in relation to organized criminal gangs involved in human trafficking and organized prostitution activities;
- employing special investigation methods in relation to the identified targets;
- work closely with and under the direction and direct supervision of the specialized prosecutor attached to the Bucharest Criminal Court;
- liaise with local actors involved in the anti-trafficking process –  IOM, Border Police, NGO's, local authorities etc.
- participate as an observer at the specialized anti-trafficking seminars and conferences organized by various local stakeholders;
- plan and conduct specialized and targeted control activities as a prevention exercise, at artistic and modeling agencies, advertising recruitment in various fields of work, particularly abroad, in well established destination countries.
